item.title: GZipper
item.dc:creator: @Patrickftw Patrickftw
item.description:
@Patrickftw wrote:

Here’s a tut/gzipper from my tutorial on a different community.

First, Download this gzipper. I virus scanned it myself.

http://uppit.com/7EHRCF

Now, Install it. Most tutorials say open run and go to the bin, Well, Heres what you can do for an easier way. Open any folder, Go to the adress bar and type

C:\Program Files\GnuWin32\bin

Drag a model into that folder.

Now, Go to

Start Menu > Run > Cmd > cd C:\Program Files\GnuWin32\bin

Type in

gzip ModelID.Dat

e.g.

gzip 15503.dat

Now, it will appear in the bin, Rename the model 4444, Or something, Any number you want.

Now you can change

gfx.anInt405 = 1337;

To the gzipped model, And there we go! You’re all done, It’s quite easy.
